          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "About 15 ug of 253Es was irradiated in a quartz vial",
                "in the Savannah River Plant high flux reactor for 36 h.",
                "After the 254Fm had grown into equilibrium with its",
                "39.3-h 254mEs parent, fermium was separated from",
                "einsteinium by cation-exchange elution development",
                "chromatography with ammonium alpha hydroxyisobutyrate.",
                "The fermium fraction was collected on a platinum plate,",
                "dried, and flamed. An aluminum-catcher-foil technique",
                "was used to collect the fission fragments from the",
                "3.24-h 254Fm source. Two catcher foils were exposed,",
                "the first for direct gamma-ray analysis and the second",
                "for radiochemical analysis."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "METHOD": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "GSPEC"
